description.p:
In one aspect of the invention is a liquid cleansing composition, including but not limited to:
a. 5 to 30 % by wt. of total synthetic anionic surfactant(s);
b. 0.5 to 5 % by wt. of total hydrophobically modified cross-linked acrylate copolymer(s);
c. 0.5 to 5 % by wt. of total normal C8 to C16 alkyl carboxylic acid(s); preferably C12 to C16, or more preferably C12 carboxylic acid(s), wherein at least 90% by wt. of the total normal carboxylic acid(s) is C12 normal carboxylic acid);
d. wherein the wt. % ratio range of the total hydrophobically modified acrylate copolymer(s) to the total normal alkyl carboxylic acid(s) is 0.1 to 3; preferably 0.3 to 1;
e. wherein the composition has a pH range of 6.8 to 7.8 for ;
f. wherein the composition contains less than 0.5 % by wt. of total oil(s) and waxes selected from hydrocarbons, triglycerides and silicones with a number average particle size under 1000 microns (preferably under 500 microns ); and
g. wherein the Standard Delta zero shear viscosity ratio of the liquid cleansing composition is more than 2 in the case of the hydrophobically modified acrylate copolymer(s) effect or more than 30 in the case of the total normal C8 to C16 alkyl carboxylic acid(s) effect.

Sulfosuccinates may be monoalkyl sulfosuccinates having the formula:



        R4O2CCH2CH(SO3M)CO2M;



and amide-MEA sulfosuccinates of the formula;



        R4CONHCH2CH2O2CCH2CH(SO3M)CO2M



wherein R4 ranges from C8-C22 alkyl and M is a solubilizing cation.

Preferred nonionic surfactants include carboxylic acid/alcohol ethoxylates having the following structures:

a) HOCH2(CH2)n(CH2CH2O)x H or
b) HOOC(CH2)m(CH2CH2O)y H;

where m, n are independently < 18; and x, y are independently > 1; preferably m, n are independently 6 to 18; x, y are independently 1 to 30;
c) HOOC(CH2)i-CH=CH-(CH2)k(CH2CH2O)z H;

where i, k are independently 5 to 15; and z is independently 5 to 50; preferably i, k are independently 6 to 12; and z is independently 15 to 35.

Hydrophobic emollients with weight average particle sizes below either 1000 or 500 microns in diameter are defined herein as "finely dispersed oils" and are in another embodiment present at total levels of less than about 0.5, 0.4, 0.3, 0.2 or 0.1 % by wt. in the inventive composition and may be absent from the composition. These hydrophobic emollients include but are not limited to the following:
(a) silicone oils and modifications thereof such as linear and cyclic polydimethylsiloxanes; amino, alkyl, alkylaryl, and aryl silicone oils;
(b) fats and oils including natural fats and oils (triglycerides) such as jojoba, soybean, sunflower, rice bran, avocado, almond, olive, sesame, persic, castor, coconut, mink oils; cacao fat; beef tallow, lard; hardened oils obtained by hydrogenating the aforementioned oils; and synthetic mono, di and triglycerides such as myristic acid glyceride and 2-ethylhexanoic acid glyceride;
(c) waxes such as carnauba, spermaceti, beeswax, lanolin, and derivatives thereof;
(d) hydrophobic plant extracts;
(e) hydrocarbons such as petrolatum, polybutene, liquid paraffins, microcrystalline wax, ceresin, squalene, pristan and mineral oil;
(f) higher alcohols such as lauryl, cetyl, stearyl, oleyl, behenyl, cholesterol and 2-hexydecanol alcohol;
(g) esters such as cetyl octanoate, myristyl lactate, cetyl lactate, isopropyl myristate, myristyl myristate, isopropyl palmitate, isopropyl adipate, butyl stearate, decyl oleate, cholesterol isostearate, glycerol monostearate, glycerol distearate, glycerol tristearate, alkyl lactate, alkyl citrate and alkyl tartrate;
(h) essential oils and extracts thereof such as mentha, jasmine, camphor, white cedar, bitter orange peel, ryu, turpentine, cinnamon, bergamot, citrus unshiu, calamus, pine, lavender, bay, clove, hiba, eucalyptus, lemon, starflower, thyme, peppermint, rose, sage, sesame, ginger, basil, juniper, lemon grass, rosemary, rosewood, avocado, grape, grapeseed, myrrh, cucumber, watercress, calendula, elder flower, geranium, linden blossom, amaranth, seaweed, ginko, ginseng, carrot, guarana, tea tree, jojoba, comfrey, oatmeal, cocoa, neroli, vanilla, green tea, penny royal, aloe vera, menthol, cineole, eugenol, citral, citronelle, borneol, linalool, geraniol, evening primrose, camphor, thymol, spirantol, penene, limonene and terpenoid oils;
(i) mixtures of any of the foregoing components, and the like.

claim.claim-text:
Flüssige Reinigungszusammensetzung, umfassend:
a. 5 bis 30 Gew.-% an Gesamtmenge von synthetischem anionischem Surfactant (synthetischen anionischen Surfactants);
b. 0,5 bis 5 Gew.-% an Gesamtmenge von hydrophob modifiziertem vernetztem Acrylatcopolymer (modifizierten vernetzten Acrylatcopolymeren);
c. 0,5 bis 5 Gew.-% an Gesamtmenge von normaler C8-C16-Alkylcarbonsäure (von normalen C8-C16-Alkylcarbonsäuren), wobei wenigstens 90 Gew.-% der Gesamtmenge von normaler Carbonsäure (normalen Carbonsäuren) normale C12-Carbonsäure ist;
d. wobei der Gewichtsverhältnisbereich der Gesamtmenge von hydrophob modifiziertem Acrylatcopolymer (hydrophob modifizierten Acrylatcopolymeren) zu der Gesamtmenge von normaler Alkylcarbonsäure (normalen Alkylcarbonsäuren) 0,1 bis 3 ist;
e. wobei die Zusammensetzung einen pH-Bereich von 6,8 bis 7,8 hat;
f. wobei die Zusammensetzung weniger als 0,5 Gew.-% an Gesamtmenge von Öl(en) und Wachsen, ausgewählt aus Kohlenwasserstoffen, Triglyceriden und Siliconen, mit einer durchschnittlichen Partikelgröße von unter 1000 Mikrometer enthält und
g. wobei das Standard-Delta-Nullscherungs-Viskositätsverhältnis, wie es hierin definiert ist, bei 25 °C der flüssigen Reinigungszusammensetzung mehr als 2 im Fall des Effektes des hydrophob modifizierten Acrylatcopolymers (der hydrophob modifizierten Acrylatcopolymeren) ist oder mehr als 30 im Fall des Effektes der normalen C8-C16-Alkylcarbonsäure(n) ist.

A liquid cleansing composition, comprising:
a. 5 to 30 % by wt. of total synthetic anionic surfactant(s);
b. 0.5 to 5 % by wt. of total hydrophobically modified cross-linked acrylate copolymer(s);
c. 0.5 to 5 % by wt. of total normal C8 to C16 alkyl carboxylic acid(s) wherein at least 90% by wt. of the total normal carboxylic acid(s) is C12 normal carboxylic acid;
d. wherein the wt. % ratio range of the total hydrophobically modified acrylate copolymer(s) to the total normal alkyl carboxylic acid(s) is 0.1 to 3;
e. wherein the composition has a pH range of 6.8 to 7.8;
f. wherein the composition contains less than 0.5 % by wt. of total oil(s) and waxes selected from hydrocarbons, triglycerides and silicones with a number average particle size under 1000 microns; and
g. wherein the Standard Delta zero shear viscosity ratio as defined herein at 25°C of the liquid cleansing composition is more than 2 in the case of the hydrophobically modified acrylate copolymer(s) effect or more than 30 in the case of the total normal C8 to C16 alkyl carboxylic acid(s) effect.

Composition liquide de nettoyage, comprenant :
a. 5 % à 30 % en poids d'un ou de plusieurs tensioactifs anioniques synthétiques totaux ;
b. 0,5 % à 5 % en poids d'un ou de plusieurs copolymères d'acrylate réticulés à modification hydrophobe totaux ;
c. 0,5 % à 5 % en poids d'un ou de plusieurs acides (alkyl en C8 à C16)-carboxyliques normaux totaux, dans laquelle au moins 90 % en poids de l'acide ou des acides carboxyliques normaux totaux est de l'acide carboxylique normal en C12 ;
d. dans laquelle la plage des rapports de % en poids entre le ou les copolymères d'acrylate à modification hydrophobe totaux et le ou les acides alkylcarboxyliques normaux totaux va de 0,1 à 3 ;
e. dans laquelle le pH de la composition est dans une plage allant de 6,8 à 7,8 ;
f. dans laquelle la composition contient moins de 0,5 % en poids d'une ou de plusieurs huiles et de cires totales choisies parmi les hydrocarbures, les triglycérides et les silicones ayant une taille de particule moyenne en nombre inférieure à 1000 microns ; et
g. dans laquelle le taux de viscosité à cisaillement nul en delta standard, tel que défini ici à 25°C, de la composition liquide de nettoyage est supérieur à 2 dans le cas de l'effet du ou des copolymères d'acrylate à modification hydrophobe ou supérieur à 30 dans le cas de l'effet du ou des acides (alkyl en C8 à C16) -carboxyliques normaux totaux.
